benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/customFields - Retrieve bundle custom fields

covered: Valid Request: TC01 demonstrates successful GET for an existing bundleId, validating 200 response and JSON array of CustomField objects with default audit (NONE).
Empty Response: TC04 covers an existing bundleId with no custom fields, returning 200 and an empty JSON array.

Query Parameters: Tests exercise query parameter handling including FULL/MINIMAL audit (TC02, TC03), invalid audit (TC07), extra parameters ignored (TC10), and malformed audit (TC13) and XSS in audit parameter (TC18).
Authorization: TC08 verifies 401 Unauthorized when no valid auth token is provided.
Error Handling: Tests cover 404 when bundle not found (TC05), 400 for invalid bundleId (TC06, TC17), and 503 when dependencies fail (TC09, TC16).
Security: SQL injection in bundleId (TC17) and XSS attempt in audit parameter (TC18).
Performance/Regression: Long-running performance scenario (TC14) and regression case (TC15) are included, plus audit-service integration failure case (TC16).
Accessibility/Structure: TC20 asserts Content-Type is application/json and body is valid JSON array.
gaps: Pagination: No tests covering API pagination (page/size) for large result sets.
Rate Limiting: No tests validating behavior under burst requests or 429 handling.
Caching Behavior: No tests verifying caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control) or conditional requests.
Authorization: No test for 403 Forbidden (authenticated but lacking permissions).
Internal Server Error: No test simulating 500 responses beyond 503 service unavailability; adding 500 tests could be beneficial.
recommendations: Add pagination tests with page and pageSize parameters to verify correct subset results and total counts.
Add a test for 403 Forbidden to cover authorization scenarios where the user is authenticated but not permitted.
Add rate-limiting tests to verify proper handling of bursts (e.g., 429 Too Many Requests).
Add caching tests to validate ETag and Cache-Control headers and If-None-Match behavior.
Add internal server error tests (500) to cover unexpected server failures beyond service unavailability.
Extend security tests with additional SQL-injection patterns and XSS vectors and verify input sanitization in all fields.
